  "modName": "Smooth Attribute Scaling",
  "summary": "Scales your attributes as with skill level instead of character level.",
  "descriptionHtml": "This mod pushes leveling further into the background by scaling your health, stamina, magicka, and carry weight with your skills instead of your character level.\r<br />\r<br />Each time you increase a skill, your attributes will be recalculated, granting you a small boost. The amount that each skill contributes to your various attributes can be configured through a Mod Configuration Menu.\r<br />\r<br />The default values are simply the ones that I use. Your character will start out more powerful than in Vanilla (approximately 150 health and 120 magicka and stamina) but you will spend the majority of the game in a comparable state. (Vanilla stats would catch up to mod stats around level 10.)\r<br />\r<br />Carry weight scales according to a combination of your health, stamina, and magicka. The benefit of each can be configured in the MCM.\r<br />\r<br />Unfortunately you will still be asked to choose an attribute to increase each time you level up. Choose any attribute. It doesn&#39;t matter. Your attributes will be recalculated when you are finished with the leveling process.\r<br />\r<br />NOW WITH LEGENDARY SUPPORT",
